# Trivy ignore file (referenced by .github/actions/iac-checks via TRIVY_IGNOREFILE).
# Reviewed, deliberately-accepted misconfiguration findings. IDs only match the resources
# they describe, so this is safe to share across all infra template scans.
#
# Azure customer-provisioning template — two network-restriction checks that cannot be
# default-on without breaking provisioning: the alethia runner applies these from OUTSIDE
# Azure (Hetzner fleet), so a default-Deny key-vault ACL or an IP-locked AKS API server
# would block the runner's own data-plane / control-plane access. Left customer-configurable
# per environment. (RBAC — AVD-AZU-0042 — IS genuinely fixed in the AKS module.)
AVD-AZU-0013
AVD-AZU-0041
